    {
      "id": "PopularPost87267",
      "post_content": "I'm not really sure which color has the best land destruction... Red has a good deal of solid spells, but so does black, and white has [Armageddon](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Armageddon) ...   \nAnyway, Stone Rain is probably the most commonly used land destruction spell (?). Though it may not be a [Pillage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillage), it still retains a decent manacost of 3, and is easy to splash for.  \n  \nAs for why this didn't get reprinted after 9th edition, I think it's because some players REALLY hate land destruction. I mean, it's a lot of fun to play with a land destruction deck, but playing against it becomes a pain - the only real action you get to take, is to draw a card at the beginning of your turn, and discarding excess cards at the end of your turn :/  \n  \nAlso, if you want to play with a land destruction deck, you might wanna run Magnivore, since most land destruction spells are sorceries.  \n  \nEDIT: oh yeah, if you splash white, you could also run [Ajani Vengeant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ajani Vengeant)",
      "posted_by": "GrimjawxRULES",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost87267\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">I'm not really sure which color has the best land destruction... Red has a good deal of solid spells, but so does black, and white has <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Armageddon\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Armageddon\">Armageddon</a> ... <br/>Anyway, Stone Rain is probably the most commonly used land destruction spell (?). Though it may not be a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Pillage\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pillage\">Pillage</a>, it still retains a decent manacost of 3, and is easy to splash for.<br/><br/>As for why this didn't get reprinted after 9th edition, I think it's because some players REALLY hate land destruction. I mean, it's a lot of fun to play with a land destruction deck, but playing against it becomes a pain - the only real action you get to take, is to draw a card at the beginning of your turn, and discarding excess cards at the end of your turn :/<br/><br/>Also, if you want to play with a land destruction deck, you might wanna run Magnivore, since most land destruction spells are sorceries.<br/><br/>EDIT: oh yeah, if you splash white, you could also run <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ajani Vengeant\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ajani Vengeant\">Ajani Vengeant</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '87267'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                         